etymologies: Middle English; earliest use found in Havelok. From Anglo-Norman rouncie, runci, runcin, Anglo-Norman and Old French, Middle French roncin, Old French ronci, (Picardy) ronsi horse used for carrying burdens from post-classical Latin runcinus, further etymology uncertain and disputed: see Französisches etymol. Wörterbuch at *runcinus

definitions: A horse, especially one used for riding; a steed.
